originalText.text: Horrible experience at this location due to staff incompetence (mainly the manager - Rachel) . I visited the store to buy some things for my daughter. I made two separate purchases, first using my foreign credit card. I was told my foreign card didn't go through. Then I used my American credit card and also cash to complete the purchase. Later on in the day, after checking my bank statement I realized that my foreign card was charged as well. So basically I was charged twice for both my purchases. Called the store and asked to speak to the manager (Rachel). her attitude from the get go was so rude and she didn't want to be bothered. I had to go back at the store and speak with her in person. She recognized the mistake as i presented her with facts,  but told me this is my problem and not hers, and that there nothing she could do. That I have to figure it out with my foreign bank, while admitting that it was the store's mistake. It was clear to me she didn't know how to do the reimbursement. Finally, after 20 min of full blown attitude on her end, and after she pressed some buttons on the cash register, she claimed she was able to give me the full refund. She printed the receipt and handed it to me, 'apologizing' for the inconvenience. My mistake was i didn't check the return receipt right there. Later on that day i decided to take a look at it and realized she hadn't reimbursed me the full amount. Now i have to call customer service and file a formal complain. That manager is way too professionally immature and incompetent  to handle the store and the customers. Not sure what criteria does the upper management use to select store managers, but they dropped the ball on this one. Needless to say I will never shop this brand ever again.
